            <svg class="icon gblog_link"><use xlink:href="#gblog_link"></use></svg>
        </a>
    </h2>
</div><p>If you want to customize the theme&rsquo;s color scheme to give it your individual touch, you are only a few lines of CSS away. Generally, you need to override the default settings. The easiest way to do this is to create a file named <code>static/custom.css</code> right at the root of your site.</p>
